To validate a password, it can go through the following process:
1ï¸) A client enters the password.
2ï¸) The system fetches the corresponding salt from the database.
3ï¸) The system appends the salt to the password and hashes it. Letâ€™s call the hashed value H1.
4ï¸) The system compares H1 and H2, where H2 is the hash stored in the database. If they are the same, the password is valid. 
 
